## Goal
Build the retro Move UI ŌĆö the window frame, Clippy-style assistant + reminder bubble, settings/loadout/catalog/tag/progress panels ŌĆö wire them into `App.tsx` via `useMove` + `useReminderEngine`, apply the late-'90s MS-Office retro styling in `index.css`, and cover the flows with integration tests.

## Context
Final assembly ticket. All logic, hooks, and PWA infra are already merged; this ticket only composes React components (named-function components with a local `XProps` type, Tailwind v4 CSS-first + CSS variables) and wires state. `App.tsx`/`App.test.tsx` currently hold a throwaway shell from the foundation ticket ŌĆö rewrite them fully. Adapt all hook/module imports to their actual merged signatures.

**Design target (carry verbatim to the worker):** the retro late-'90s MS Office / Clippy aesthetic derives from `ai-design/frontendstyle.jpg`. That file is forbidden/gitignored ŌĆö NEVER open or modify it; build the beveled retro look (window chrome, yellow speech balloon, gray 3D borders) to match it using custom CSS in `src/index.css`.

## Acceptance criteria
- New components under `src/components/`: `RetroWindow.tsx`, `Assistant.tsx`, `ReminderBubble.tsx`, `SettingsPanel.tsx`, `LoadoutLibrary.tsx`, `ExerciseCatalog.tsx`, `TagRuleEditor.tsx`, `ProgressPanel.tsx`.
- `src/App.tsx` composes them inside `RetroWindow`, wiring `useMove` + `useReminderEngine`.
- `src/index.css` keeps `@import 'tailwindcss';` and defines a retro palette + beveled component styling per `ai-design/frontendstyle.jpg`.
- Reminders START PAUSED with a visible **Start** control; a fresh visitor sees the default "Office-safe" loadout.
- `npm run lint`, `npm run build`, `npm test` pass.

## File changes
Sketches are guidance; adapt to the actual merged hooks/modules.

### `src/components/RetroWindow.tsx` (new)
