### `src/components/SettingsPanel.tsx` (new)
Interval + snooze number inputs (positive integers, min 1), the Start/Stop control (calls `engine.start()`/`engine.stop()`), the context selector (lists `context`-axis tags; calls `setContext`), and the equipment checklist (lists `equipment`-axis tags; toggles `ownedEquipment` via `toggleEquipment`).

### `src/components/LoadoutLibrary.tsx` (new)
List loadouts, show the active one, switch active (`setActiveLoadout`), create/edit (embeds `TagRuleEditor`), export (build a bundle and offer it as a download/text) and import (parse text, call `importBundle`). Surface size/completeness/safety errors from `importBundle` to the user, and render the axis-conflict keep-or-rename choice UI when `importBundle` reports conflicts.

### `src/components/ExerciseCatalog.tsx` (new)
List exercises; add-custom form (name, instructions, structured target reps|time, image upload validated with `isSafeImage` + `MAX_IMAGE_BYTES`, tags) that calls `addExercise`; mint a tag inline via an explicit **axis picker** (calls `addTag(name, axis)`).

### `src/components/TagRuleEditor.tsx` (new)
Edit a loadout's include / require-all / exclude tag-name lists; minting a new tag here ALWAYS shows a visible axis picker (calls `addTag(name, axis)`).

### `src/components/ProgressPanel.tsx` (new)
Show done count, ignored/skipped count, and current-day streak from `deriveStats`. Primary factual line "Sitting breaks taken: N" WITH the `Diaz et al., Annals of Internal Medicine, 2017` citation; a secondary "Ōēł N├Ś2 active minutes" line CLEARLY labelled a playful estimate (no citation).

### `src/App.tsx` (rewrite from the foundation shell)
```tsx
function App() {
  const move = useMove()
  const engine = useReminderEngine(/* move.state, move.recordAction, sw registration, ... */)
  return (
    <RetroWindow title="Move">
      <Assistant current={engine.current} onAction={engine.handleAction} />
      <SettingsPanel ... running={engine.running} onStart={engine.start} onStop={engine.stop} />
      <LoadoutLibrary ... /> <ExerciseCatalog ... /> <ProgressPanel ... />
    </RetroWindow>
  )
}
export default App
```

