## Test expectations
- `src/App.test.tsx` (rewrite): a fresh visitor sees the "Move" title, a **Start** control, reminders paused (no active reminder bubble), and the default "Office-safe" loadout active; the mint UI exposes an axis picker; creating a custom exercise tagged with a newly minted axis-tagged tag makes it selectable/eligible; switching the active loadout changes the eligible set. Use role/label queries and `localStorage.clear()` in `beforeEach`.
- Optionally colocate small component tests (e.g. `ReminderBubble.test.tsx` asserting name/`formatTarget`/instructions render and each of Done/Skip/Snooze/Shuffle fires `onAction`; `ProgressPanel.test.tsx` asserting the citation appears on the factual figure and the estimate line is labelled). Prefer covering flows through `App.test.tsx`.

## Out of scope
Changing logic modules, hooks, storage, or PWA infra (consume them as-is). Do not open or modify `ai-design/frontendstyle.jpg`.

## Goal
Add the installable-PWA infrastructure ŌĆö web manifest, a plain-JS service worker with runtime caching and a `notificationclick` action pipeline, shipped static assets, `index.html` metadata, and service-worker registration in `main.tsx`.

## Context
Move is an installable PWA with no static precache list ŌĆö the service worker caches at runtime. The SW is plain JS in `public/` (out of `src`) so no WebWorker types leak into `tsconfig`. This ticket is largely self-contained and touches disjoint files from the logic tickets; it only needs the app to render (the App shell already exists).

## Acceptance criteria
- `public/manifest.webmanifest`, `public/sw.js`, `public/icons/*` (at least 192px and 512px PNG), `public/exercises/placeholder.png` (a small real PNG), and `public/ding.wav` (a tiny real WAV) exist.
- `index.html` has `<title>Move</title>`, a `<link rel="manifest" href="/manifest.webmanifest">`, and a `theme-color` meta.
- `src/main.tsx` registers `/sw.js` (guarded by `'serviceWorker' in navigator`) and posts `client-ready` to the controller once mounted.
- `sw.js` implements the caching + `notificationclick` behavior below.
- `npm run lint`, `npm run build`, `npm test` pass (existing tests remain green).

## File changes
Sketches are guidance; adapt to actual file state.

