## Test expectations
No new unit tests are required for `sw.js` (plain JS, out of the Vitest/jsdom scope) or the binary assets. Do NOT break the existing suite: `main.tsx` changes must be guarded so `npm test` and `npm run build` stay green. If you add any importable helper, colocate a small `*.test.ts`.

## Out of scope
The engine hook that consumes SW messages (already implemented elsewhere), notification firing logic, and visual components. Do not modify `src/types.ts` or logic modules.

## Goal
Implement the two React hooks ŌĆö `useMove` (owns `MoveState`, auto-persists on real change, merges cross-tab `storage` events) and `useReminderEngine` (ephemeral running/current, leader-gated timer with failover, snooze, empty-pool resume, SW-action draining) ŌĆö with tests using fake timers.

## Context
`useMove` is the single state-owning hook (analogous to the old `useBoard`); `useReminderEngine` drives reminders only in the elected leader tab. Depends on foundation (`types`, `catalog`, `id`, `selection`) plus `storage` (t2), `progress` (t2), `loadouts` (t3), and `notifications`/`sound`/`engineChannel` (t4). Adapt imports to those modules' actual exports.

## Acceptance criteria
- `src/hooks/useMove.ts` exports `useMove()` returning `{ state, ...mutators }` (mutators below), auto-persisting only when the serialized state changed, and reconciling `storage` events via `mergeState` only when the serialized form differs.
- `src/hooks/useReminderEngine.ts` exports `useReminderEngine(...)` returning `{ running, current, start, stop, handleAction }`.
- All mutators stamp `updatedAt` on the entities they change.
- `npm run lint`, `npm run build`, `npm test` pass.

## File changes
Sketches are guidance; adapt to actual merged modules.

### `src/hooks/useMove.ts` (new)
```ts
import { useEffect, useRef, useState } from 'react'
import { loadState, mergeState, saveState, serialize, STORAGE_KEY } from '../storage'
import { importBundle as importBundleFn } from '../loadouts'
import { newId } from '../id'
import { normalizeTag } from '../catalog'

export function useMove() {
  const [state, setState] = useState(loadState)
  const lastSerialized = useRef(serialize(state))
  // Persist only on real change.
  useEffect(() => {
    const s = serialize(state)
    if (s === lastSerialized.current) return
    lastSerialized.current = s
    saveState(state)
  }, [state])
  // Cross-tab: on storage event for STORAGE_KEY, reload, mergeState, and setState ONLY if the
  // serialized merged form differs from lastSerialized (prevents save<->merge ping-pong).
  useEffect(() => { /* addEventListener('storage', ...) + cleanup */ }, [])
  // Mutators (each stamps updatedAt on touched entities and returns via setState):
  //   setInterval(min), setSnooze(min), setContext(name), toggleEquipment(name),
  //   setActiveLoadout(id), addExercise(draft), addTag(name, axis) [normalizeTag + dedupe by name],
  //   saveLoadout(loadout), importBundle(raw, opts), recordAction(occurrenceId, exerciseId, action).
  //   recordAction appends a HistoryEntry { id: newId(), occurrenceId, exerciseId, action, at }.
  return { state, setInterval: setIntervalMin, setSnooze, setContext, toggleEquipment, setActiveLoadout, addExercise, addTag, saveLoadout, importBundle, recordAction }
}
```
Note: name the interval mutator so it does not shadow the global `setInterval` (e.g. `setIntervalMinutes`).

### `src/hooks/useReminderEngine.ts` (new)
```ts
import { useEffect, useRef, useState } from 'react'
import { eligiblePool, selectNext } from '../selection'
import { trimHistory } from '../progress'
import { createEngineChannel } from '../engineChannel'
import { fireReminder, requestPermission } from '../notifications'
import { playDing } from '../sound'
import { MAX_DELAY_MS } from '../catalog'
import { newId } from '../id'

// useReminderEngine({ state, recordAction, setState/trim hook, swRegistration }):
//   ephemeral state: running (bool), current ({ exercise, occurrenceId } | null). NEVER persisted.
//   start(): await requestPermission(); running = true; (re)start the leader loop.
//   Leader loop (only while isLeader()): every settings.intervalMinutes a tick fires:
//     pool = eligiblePool(state). If EMPTY: show the assistant "no eligible exercises ŌĆö adjust your
//       loadout", play NO ding/notification, but STILL reschedule the next tick (loadout switch resumes
//       automatically). Else: ex = selectNext(pool, lastId); occurrenceId = newId(); set current;
//       playDing(); fireReminder(swRegistration, ex, occurrenceId); leader-only trimHistory of state.
//   setTimeout delays are clamped to MAX_DELAY_MS.
//   handleAction({ action, occurrenceId, exerciseId }): recordAction(...) is allowed in ANY tab.
//     STATE TRANSITIONS are LEADER-ONLY; a non-leader relays via engineChannel.relayAction and does
//     nothing else. Clear/advance only affects `current` when occurrenceId === current.occurrenceId
//     (a stale notification records its action but never dismisses an unrelated active reminder).
//       done/skip => clear current. shuffle => re-pick (new occurrenceId), WITHOUT recording done.
//       snooze => mint a NEW occurrenceId for the rescheduled fire; arm a snooze timer KEYED by the
//         triggering occurrenceId (arming replaces any existing timer for that key); broadcastSnooze
//         so a new leader adopts it.
//   engineChannel handlers: onAction => apply as leader; onAdoptSnooze => arm keyed snooze timer.
//   On mount: drain any pending SW-queued actions (listen for navigator.serviceWorker 'message'
//     {type:'reminder-action'} and process the queue), then post 'client-ready' is done in main.tsx.
//   Cleanup: clear timers, engineChannel.close().
export function useReminderEngine(/* ... */) { /* ... */ return { running, current, start, stop, handleAction } }
```

## Test expectations
- `src/hooks/useMove.test.ts` (or `.tsx`): with `@testing-library/react` `renderHook`, an incoming `storage` event carrying an equal-but-reordered serialized state does NOT trigger a re-save (spy on `saveState`/`localStorage.setItem`); a mutator stamps `updatedAt` and persists once.
- `src/hooks/useReminderEngine.test.ts` (fake timers; mock `notifications`, `sound`, `engineChannel`): an interval fire calls `fireReminder` and `playDing`; a snooze re-fire uses a NEW `occurrenceId`; a huge `intervalMinutes` clamps the `setTimeout` delay to `MAX_DELAY_MS`; `handleAction` with `occurrenceId !== current.occurrenceId` does NOT clear the active reminder but still records; shuffle advances without recording `done`; a non-leader relays and applies no transition; leader resign/timeout lets a peer continue; an empty pool still reschedules the next tick; a pending SW-queued action is drained on mount.

## Out of scope
The service worker file and `main.tsx` (another ticket), and all visual components. Consume the already-merged modules; do not modify them beyond importing.

## Goal
Implement the three browser-integration modules ŌĆö notification firing (rich vs fallback), the retro ding, and the `BroadcastChannel` leader-election/relay layer ŌĆö each guarded for jsdom/absent APIs and unit-tested.

## Context
Move fires exercise reminders via the Notifications API and coordinates a single active timer across tabs via `BroadcastChannel('move.engine')`. All three modules must feature-detect and degrade gracefully (jsdom has neither `Notification`, `Audio`, nor a useful `BroadcastChannel`). Depends on `src/types.ts`, `src/catalog.ts` (`formatTarget`), and `src/id.ts` (`newId`).

## Acceptance criteria
- `src/notifications.ts` exports `requestPermission`, `maxInlineActions`, `orderedActions`, `fireReminder`.
- `src/sound.ts` exports `playDing`.
- `src/engineChannel.ts` exports `createEngineChannel` returning the API below, with a no-op shim when `BroadcastChannel` is unavailable.
- Every DOM/global access is guarded so the modules import cleanly under jsdom.
- `npm run lint`, `npm run build`, `npm test` pass.

## File changes
Sketches are guidance; adapt to actual foundation state.

