### `src/engineChannel.ts` (new)
```ts
import { newId } from './id'

export type ReminderMsg = { type: 'reminder'; exerciseId: string; occurrenceId: string }
export type ActionMsg = { type: 'action'; action: string; occurrenceId: string; exerciseId: string; actionEventId: string }
export type SnoozeMsg = { type: 'snooze'; key: string; exerciseId: string; fireAt: number }

export type EngineHandlers = {
  onBecomeLeader?: () => void
  onLoseLeader?: () => void
  onAction?: (msg: ActionMsg) => void       // leader applies relayed actions
  onAdoptSnooze?: (msg: SnoozeMsg) => void   // new leader adopts a still-future snooze
}

// createEngineChannel(handlers):
//   - If typeof BroadcastChannel === 'undefined', return a no-op shim whose isLeader() === true
//     (each tab runs its own engine; duplicate notifications possible ŌĆö documented).
//   - Otherwise open BroadcastChannel('move.engine'). Assign a stable tabPriority = newId().
//     Election: broadcast candidacy; LOWEST tabPriority wins (deterministic tiebreak).
//     Leader emits a heartbeat every 2s. A non-leader that sees no heartbeat for 6s re-runs election.
//     On pagehide / visibilitychange(hidden) / beforeunload the leader broadcasts an explicit 'resign'.
//     relayAction: non-leader sends ActionMsg (with actionEventId = newId()) to the leader and RETRIES
//       until acked or the effect is observed; the leader keeps a short-lived processed set of
//       actionEventIds, applies each once via onAction, and ACKs. broadcastSnooze sends SnoozeMsg;
//       a newly elected leader adopts any still-future snooze via onAdoptSnooze (keyed by SnoozeMsg.key).
export function createEngineChannel(handlers: EngineHandlers): {
  isLeader: () => boolean
  relayAction: (a: Omit<ActionMsg, 'type' | 'actionEventId'>) => void
  broadcastSnooze: (s: Omit<SnoozeMsg, 'type'>) => void
  close: () => void
} { /* ... */ }
```
Note: timers (heartbeat/failover) must use real `setInterval`/`setTimeout` so tests can drive them with fake timers.

## Test expectations
- `src/notifications.test.ts`: `orderedActions(2)` returns `['done','snooze']` (priority truncation); `orderedActions(0)` returns `[]`; with a mocked `registration.showNotification`, `fireReminder` sets title = exercise name, body includes `formatTarget(target)`, and `data` carries `{ occurrenceId, exerciseId }`; falls back to plain `Notification` when `maxInlineActions()` is 0. Stub `Notification`/`ServiceWorkerRegistration` as needed.
- `src/sound.test.ts`: `playDing` does not throw when `Audio` is undefined and, with a mocked `Audio`, constructs `'/ding.wav'` and swallows a rejected `play()`.
- `src/engineChannel.test.ts` (fake timers + a mock `BroadcastChannel` that fans messages to peer instances): lowest-`tabPriority` wins election; a heartbeat timeout AND an explicit resign each trigger re-election; a relayed action with an `actionEventId` is applied once and NOT double-applied across a simulated mid-processing leader death + retry (single effect); an armed-snooze broadcast is adopted (`onAdoptSnooze`) by a newly elected leader; the no-`BroadcastChannel` shim reports `isLeader() === true`.

## Out of scope
The engine hook that consumes this (`useReminderEngine`), the service worker file, and UI. Do not modify foundation modules beyond importing.

## Goal
Implement `exportBundle` and `importBundle` for shareable loadout bundles, with size/safety/referential-completeness guards, id-collision handling, normalized tag merge, and axis-conflict keep-or-rename ŌĆö unit-tested.

## Context
A user exports a loadout as a self-contained JSON bundle `{ version: 1, loadout, exercises, tags }` and imports it elsewhere. Bundles are UNTRUSTED. This is pure TS depending on `src/types.ts`, `src/catalog.ts`, and `src/selection.ts` (uses `matchesLoadout`).

## Acceptance criteria
- `src/loadouts.ts` exports `exportBundle(state, loadoutId): LoadoutBundle` and `importBundle(state, raw, opts?): ImportResult`.
- All guards below are enforced up front with clear thrown `Error`s.
- `npm run lint`, `npm run build`, `npm test` pass.

## File changes
Sketches are guidance; adapt to the actual state of already-merged foundation modules.

### `src/loadouts.ts` (new)
```ts
import type { Exercise, ImportResult, Loadout, LoadoutBundle, MoveState, TagDef } from './types'
import { MAX_BUNDLE_BYTES, MAX_IMAGE_BYTES, isSafeImage, normalizeTag } from './catalog'
import { matchesLoadout } from './selection'
import { newId } from './id'

// exportBundle(state, loadoutId):
//   loadout = state.loadouts.find(id === loadoutId) (throw if missing)
//   exercises = state.exercises.filter(ex => ex.custom && matchesLoadout(ex, loadout))  // equipment/context-agnostic
//   referenced tag names = normalized union of every exercise.tags of those exercises
//     AND loadout.include/requireAll/exclude
//   tags = state.tags.filter(t => referenced.has(normalizeTag(t.name)))
//   return { version: 1, loadout, exercises, tags }
export function exportBundle(state: MoveState, loadoutId: string): LoadoutBundle { /* ... */ }

// opts: { axisConflicts?: Record<string /*normalized name*/, 'keep' | 'rename'> } (default per-name 'keep')
// importBundle(state, raw, opts?):
//   1. Parse: accept an object or a JSON string; measure byte size via
//      new TextEncoder().encode(JSON.stringify(bundle)).length <= MAX_BUNDLE_BYTES else throw.
//   2. Reject bundle.version !== 1.
//   3. Guard shape of loadout/exercises/tags; for each exercise: isSafeImage(image) else throw,
//      and image byte size (TextEncoder length) <= MAX_IMAGE_BYTES else throw.
//   4. Referential completeness: every tag name referenced by an imported exercise's tags OR by
//      the loadout's rule arrays must resolve (normalized) to a TagDef in bundle.tags UNION state.tags;
//      a missing referenced TagDef is a HARD error (throw) ŌĆö never default to 'other'.
//   5. Merge tags by normalized name into state.tags. Same name + SAME axis => keep greater updatedAt.
//      Same name + DIFFERENT axis => consult opts.axisConflicts[name]:
//        'keep'   => keep local axis, push warning { name, localAxis, bundleAxis }.
//        'rename' => mint a fresh normalized tag name carrying the BUNDLE axis, and rewrite that name
//                    in the incoming exercises' tags AND the loadout's rule arrays.
//   6. Merge exercises by id: id unused locally => keep as-is; id collides with a DIFFERENT local
//      exercise => assign a fresh newId() (no clobber; no reference remap needed ŌĆö loadouts reference
//      tag names, not exercise ids, and bundles carry no history); identical to local => skip.
//   7. Append the loadout (fresh newId() if its id collides).
//   Return { state: mergedState, warnings }.
export function importBundle(state: MoveState, raw: unknown, opts?: { axisConflicts?: Record<string, 'keep' | 'rename'> }): ImportResult { /* ... */ }
```

## Test expectations
